ActCanadian Orders, Decorations and Medals Directive, 1998
SubjectOrder Directing that the King Charles III Coronation Medal be Added to the Order of Precedence
PrecisOrder directing that the King Charles III Coronation Medal be added to the order of precedence in the Canadian Honours System under the heading “Commemorative Medals” in section 1 of the Canadian Orders, Decorations and Medals Directive, 1998, after the Queen Elizabeth II’s Diamond Jubilee Medal(2012).
